result.execSummary:
The defendant Jason Courtney Cameron Sr was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Intimidate Witness [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.42.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Certification of transcript of proceedings of SENTENCING HEARING commencing MAY 22, 2015 received and filed. (29 Pages.)
Copy of transcript forwarded to THE INSTITUTION.
Denying Request to Modify Sentence signed and filed on 7/17/15.  Copies sent to parties.  rmm
Per order of the Presiding Judge, Misdemeanor Division, this motion/request is hereby assigned to the Hon. Rebecca Dallet, Br. 40, for review. crt
Defendant's pro se request for sentence modification.

Defendant Jason Courtney Cameron in court with attorney Frederick F Klimetz.  Defendant Jason Courtney Cameron in custody.  Michael Christopher Schindhelm appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: rmm.  
Court found the state has satisfied victims' rights law.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  The Court ordered the Defendant to serve 9 months in the House of Correction, concurrent with 15CF789 with credit for 148 days time served.  Court ordered defendant to pay all applicable court costs and surcharges by the end of extended supervison in 15CF789. Cash bail in 15CF789 to apply. Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment and/or tax intercept or other means.

AS TO THE AMENDED CHARGE:  Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  Defendant further advised that if he/she is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.  Court ordered case adjourned for sentencing in Branch 40.  Court ordered defendant REMANDED into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.  Court advised defendant that the no contact order remains in effect.

Defendant Jason Courtney Cameron in court with attorney Frederick F Klimetz.  Defendant Jason Courtney Cameron in custody.  Michael Christopher Schindhelm appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: rmm.  
On motion of the State, Court ordered charge amended to Misdemeanor Intimidation, Domestic Abuse Assessments, contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 940.42, 973.055(1), a Class A Misdemeanor.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for May 22, 2015 at 08:30 am.
Bail motion by defense argued and denied by the Court.

Defendant Jason Courtney Cameron in court with attorney Frederick F Klimetz.  Defendant Jason Courtney Cameron in custody.  Michael Christopher Schindhelm appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Deputy Court Clerk: rmm.  
Final Pretrial held.  Case remains set for jury trial on 4/20/15 in Branch 40.   On motion of the state, Court ordered 14CF573, 15CF680 and 15cf789 joined for the purpose of trial.  Court reminds defendant the no contact order remains in effect.
Same conditions to apply.
Bail motion by defense argued and granted by the Court.  Bail $1000.00

Defendant Jason Courtney Cameron in court with attorney Frederick F Klimetz.  Defendant Jason Courtney Cameron in custody.  Michael Christopher Schindhelm appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Deputy Court Clerk: rmm.    
Defense counsel waived reading of the Information and entered a plea of not guilty on behalf of defendant.  Court will address state's motion for joinder on the final pretrial date.  As there are new cases and counsel is not sure he will be ready for trial on those by 4/20/15, Court ordered a backup trial date set.  Case is adjourned to Branch 40.  Court advised defendant that the no contact order remains in effect.  Final pre-trial scheduled for April 10, 2015 at 08:30 am.  Jury trial scheduled for May 18, 2015 at 08:30 am.
received and filed.  rmm
Bail motion by defense argued and denied by the Court.

Defendant Jason Courtney Cameron in court with attorney Frederick F Klimetz.  Defendant Jason Courtney Cameron in custody.  Michael Christopher Schindhelm appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: rmm.  
Preliminary hearing proceeded.  Sworn for the state:  DA Investigator Paul Bratonja.  Exhibit #1 received.   State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Case is adjourned to Branch 40.  Exhibit withdrawn.  Court advised defendant that the no contact order remains in effect.  Arraignment scheduled for March 10, 2015 at 01:30 pm.

Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION.  No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.  Defendant advised it is a requirement to attend all future court proceedings.  Failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.
Signed and filed, No Contact Order.  Defendant to have no contact with Sekeena J.; Movietta D.; or JJ dob 2/8/00

Defendant Jason Courtney Cameron in court with attorney Michael Jude.  Defendant Jason Courtney Cameron in custody.  Ronald Dague appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk:  bm
  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Dallet, Branch 40.   Defense moves to dismiss for lack of probable cause.  Arguments heard.  Court DENIES motion to dismiss.  Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold the defendant for further proceedings.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for February 26, 2015 at 01:30 pm.
